#Install PHP

1) Visit this link: http://bit.ly/1ru6wsN
2) Download the latest threaded version(32/64 bit).
3) Extract the files.
4) Copy the file to your C: drive.

#Install Composer

1) Visit this link: http://bit.ly/1t3v7eu
2) Set the path of php.exe to the php.exe in the recently copied file for php in C: drive.
3) Finish Installation and move on to Laravel.

#Install Laravel

1) Run Command Prompt.
2) Paste this command : composer global require "laravel/installer"
3) It will take some time to run.
4) Laravel has been successfully installed.
